Automotive company Isuzu Motors South Africa (IMSAf) has appointed Penelope Jabulile Mkhwanazi as the senior VP for revenue generation for the rest of Africa and international markets. In her new role, Mkhwanazi is responsible for all revenue generation in the rest of Africa markets, including sales and aftersales. She joins Isuzu from Isanti, where she held the role of CEO. “I join Isuzu at a very exciting and transformative time where our call to action is that of breakthrough and growth. The rest of Africa markets are our greatest opportunity to fulfil this call to action. “I am humbled to be part of this journey and confident that the Isuzu team will relentlessly, and with passion, answer this call to action,” she says. Mkhwanazi’s work experience spans over 20 years in various industries including manufacturing, mining, construction, fast-moving consumer goods and entrepreneurship. She obtained a BSc (Biochemistry and Microbiology) qualification from the University of the Witwatersrand in 2002 and completed a Management Development Programme from the Cyril Ramaphosa World of Learning in 2003. She went on to achieve a brewing qualification from the Institute and Guild of Brewing of London in 2003 and later achieved a Master Brewer Diploma from the same institution in 2006. In 2009, Mkhwanazi achieved a qualification as PMI Certified Associate in Project Management and an MBA from GIBS in 2011. IMSAf president and CEO Billy Tom says the Isuzu leadership is delighted to welcome Mkhwanazi on board. “Her vision for the business and extensive experience across the various sectors make her ideally suited to lead and build the long-term growth and sustainability of IMSAf in African markets,” he notes.